      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">After the lifting eyes have been mounted,
lift the transport unit to the installation location.</p>
            <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">Make sure that <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">all</u> equipment used to lift
the transport unit is rated for the weight of the transport unit.</note>
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For transport units that weigh 500 kg or more:</b>Always use a lifting traverse that strains the lifting eyes perpendicular
(90°) to the system roof.<fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/Lifting_with_lifting-eyes_more-than-500_0000376553.svg"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For transport units that
weigh 500 kg or less:</b>It is recommended to use
a lifting traverse that strains the lifting eyes perpendicular (90°)
to the system roof. Alternatively, the lifting eyes can be strained
at an angle greater than 45°.<fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/Lifting_with_lifting-eyes_less-than-499_0000376552.svg"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
